benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request: TC01 covers successful update of externalKey via PUT with proper payload and 204 response.
Authorization: TC12 covers unauthorized access scenarios; TC02 covers missing required header leading to 400.
Non-Existing Resource: TC04 (malformed ID yields 400) and TC15 (no bundles) and TC03 (malformed ID) cover non-existent resources and invalid IDs with appropriate errors.
Concurrency: TC17 tests concurrent updates to the same bundle (conflict handling).
Validation/Error Handling: TC02, TC03, TC06, TC07, TC08, TC11 cover missing headers, malformed payloads, missing/invalid fields; TC09 and TC14 cover handling of extra fields and additional headers.
Server Error Handling: TC13 covers 503 when a dependent service/database is unavailable.

Edge Cases & Variants: TC10 (very long externalKey), TC19 (special characters), TC20 (leading/trailing spaces), TC21 (extra header), TC18/TC22 (regression/backward compatibility), TC24 (documentation accessibility).
Performance/Volume: TC16 (large payload) and TC23 (response time under load) address performance considerations.
gaps: Rate Limiting: no tests to verify throttling or rate limiting behavior under bursty traffic.
Caching Behavior: no tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or client-side cache interactions.

Partial Update Semantics: PUT typically implies full update; explicit tests validating rejection of partial updates (if required by design) are not clearly present beyond handling of extra fields (TC09).
Security/Authorization depth beyond token presence: while TC12 covers unauthorized access, broader role-based access or token refresh scenarios are not explicitly tested.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure the API gracefully handles bursts or repeated requests.
Add caching/header tests to validate ETag/Cache-Control behavior and cache invalidation semantics.
Add explicit tests for Partial Update behavior if the API is designed to reject partial payloads on PUT (clarify and test).
Enhance security tests to cover broader authorization scenarios (e.g., role-based access, token expiry/refresh) and ensure consistent error messaging.
